3}=3D8.}"></span>
</p><p>The logarithm of base <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-sty=
le:italic;">b</span> is the inverse operation, that provides the output <sp=
an class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> from the in=
put <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span>. Tha=
t is, <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 y=3D\log _{b}x}">
