ic;">b</span> is a positive <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real_n=
umber" title=3D"Real number">real number</a>. (If <span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span> is not a positive real number, bo=
th exponentiation and logarithm can be defined but may take several values,=
 which makes definitions much more complicated.)
</p><p>One of the main historical motivations of introducing logarithms is =
the formula=20
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \log _{b}(xy)=3D\log _{b}x+\log _{b}y,}">
