<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Definition">Definition</h2>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLogarithm&amp;ac=
tion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Definition"><span>edit<=
/span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Given a positive <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real_number" t=
itle=3D"Real number">real number</a> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"=
font-style:italic;">b</span> such that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i> =E2=
=89=A0 1</span>, the <i>logarithm</i> of a positive real number <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> with respect to bas=
e&nbsp;<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span><s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Logarithm#cite_note-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>nb 1<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> is the exponent by which <span =
class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span> must be raised=
 to yield <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span=
>. In other words, the logarithm of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"f=
ont-style:italic;">x</span> to base&nbsp;<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span> is the unique real number&nbsp;<span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> such that <span cla=
ss=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mat=
hml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"ht=
tp://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle b^{y}=3Dx}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>b</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>y</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle b^{y}=3Dx}</a=
nnotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/7b51b8dcca3e64714e2f3aba12bb8c68812f77cc" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:6.475ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle b^{=
y}=3Dx}"></span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithm#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The logarithm is denoted "<span class=3D"texhtml">log<sub><i>b</i></=
sub>=E2=80=89<i>x</i></span>" (pronounced as "the logarithm of <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> to base&nbsp;<span =
class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span>", "the <span c=
lass=3D"nowrap">base-<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:itali=
c;">b</span></span> logarithm of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font=
-style:italic;">x</span>", or most commonly "the log, base&nbsp;<span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span>, of <span class=3D"=
texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span>").
</p><p>An equivalent and more succinct definition is that the function <spa=
n class=3D"texhtml">log<sub><i>b</i></sub></span> is the <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inverse_function" title=3D"Inverse function">inverse=
 function</a> to the function <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-elem=
ent-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" sty=
le=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" al=
ttext=3D"{\displaystyle x\mapsto b^{x}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>x</mi>
