<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Logarithmic_identities">Log=
arithmic identities</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?=
title=3DLogarithm&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section:=
 Logarithmic identities"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection=
-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article=
: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_logarithmic_identities" =
title=3D"List of logarithmic identities">List of logarithmic identities</a>=
</div>
<p>Several important formulas, sometimes called <i>logarithmic identities</=
i> or <i>logarithmic laws</i>, relate logarithms to one another.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lo=
garithm#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Product,_quotient,_power,_a=
nd_root"><span id=3D"Product.2C_quotient.2C_power.2C_and_root"></span>Produ=
ct, quotient, power, and root</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/=
index.php?title=3DLogarithm&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edi=
t section: Product, quotient, power, and root"><span>edit</span></a><span c=
lass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The logarithm of a product is the sum of the logarithms of the numbers b=
eing multiplied; the logarithm of the ratio of two numbers is the differenc=
e of the logarithms. The logarithm of the <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" styl=
e=3D"font-style:italic;">p</span>-th power of a number is <span class=3D"te=
xhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">p</span>&nbsp;times the logarithm =
of the number itself; the logarithm of a <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">p</span>-th root is the logarithm of the number div=
ided by <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">p</span>.=
