<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Change_of_base">Change of b=
ase</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLogarith=
m&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: Change of base"=
><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span=
></div>
<p>The logarithm <span class=3D"texhtml">log<sub><i>b</i></sub>=E2=80=89<i>=
x</i></span> can be computed from the logarithms of <span class=3D"texhtml =
mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar=
" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span> with respect to an arbitrary base&n=
bsp;<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">k</span> usin=
g the following formula:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithm#cite_note-6"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>nb 2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \log _{b}x=3D{\frac {\log _{k}x}{\log _{k}b}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>log</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>b</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>log</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>k</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>log</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>k</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
              <mi>b</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \log _{b}x=3D=
{\frac {\log _{k}x}{\log _{k}b}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/6575863d29b357a7ba1ce0a4c1bb93a53b19e671" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.505ex; width:15.985ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
log _{b}x=3D{\frac {\log _{k}x}{\log _{k}b}}.}"></span>
</p><p>Typical <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientific_calculat=
ors" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Scientific calculators">scientific calc=
ulators</a> calculate the logarithms to bases 10 and <span class=3D"texhtml=
 mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/E_(mathematical_constant)" title=3D"E (mathematical constant)">e</a></spa=
n>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Logarithm#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Logarithms with respect to an=
y base&nbsp;<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</sp=
an> can be determined using either of these two logarithms by the previous =
formula:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \log _{b}x=3D{\frac {\log _{10}x}{\log _{10}b}}=3D{\fra=
c {\log _{e}x}{\log _{e}b}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>log</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>b</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>log</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>10</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>log</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>10</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
              <mi>b</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>log</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>e</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>log</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>e</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
              <mi>b</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \log _{b}x=3D=
{\frac {\log _{10}x}{\log _{10}b}}=3D{\frac {\log _{e}x}{\log _{e}b}}.}</an=
notation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b69f8613162e2ae7c46c99bc72402644e16ef317" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.505ex; width:26.394ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
log _{b}x=3D{\frac {\log _{10}x}{\log _{10}b}}=3D{\frac {\log _{e}x}{\log _=
{e}b}}.}"></span>
</p><p>Given a number <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ital=
ic;">x</span> and its logarithm <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>y</i> =3D log<su=
b><i>b</i></sub>=E2=80=89<i>x</i></span> to an unknown base&nbsp;<span clas=
s=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span>, the base is given=
 by:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle b=3Dx^{\frac {1}{y}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>b</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mi>y</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle b=3Dx^{\frac =
{1}{y}},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/c3fd9660ce8c1b5ba4ef5d2f1f08a8ed5dde5a08" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.671ex; width:7.808ex; height:3.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle b=
=3Dx^{\frac {1}{y}},}"></span>
</p><p>which can be seen from taking the defining equation <span class=3D"m=
we-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inl=
ine mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://ww=
w.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle x=3Db^{\,\log _{b}x}=
=3Db^{y}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>b</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
            <msub>
              <mi>log</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi>b</mi>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>b</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>y</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle x=3Db^{\,\log=
 _{b}x}=3Db^{y}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/2311f2504e15b12a0209f669134985b6b7deac7e" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:15.356ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle x=
=3Db^{\,\log _{b}x}=3Db^{y}}"></span> to the power of <span class=3D"mwe-ma=
th-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline m=
we-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.=
org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle {\tfrac {1}{y}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mi>y</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\tfrac {1}{y=
}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/88ffe0bbb43942183114c150f227a11184b4c11e" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.338ex; width:2.305ex; height:3.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\t=
frac {1}{y}}.}"></span>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Particular_bases">Particula=
r bases<span class=3D"anchor" id=3D"log_base_anchor"></span></h2><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLogarithm&amp;action=3Dedi=
t&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: Particular bases"><span>edit</spa=
n></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Log4.svg" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img =
src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Log4.svg/3=
30px-Log4.svg.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"300" height=3D"261" class=3D=
"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"575" data-file-height=3D"500"></a><fig=
caption>Overlaid graphs of the logarithm for bases <span class=3D"sfrac">=
=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">=E2=80=AF1=E2=80=AF</span=
><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den"> 2 </span></span>=E2=
=81=A0</span>, 2, and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ital=
ic;">e</span></figcaption></figure>
<p>Among all choices for the base, three are particularly common. These are=
 <span class=3D"texhtml"> <i>b</i> =3D 10</span>, <span class=3D"texhtml"> =
<i>b</i> =3D <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E_(mathematical_const=
ant)" title=3D"E (mathematical constant)"><i>e</i></a></span> (the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Irrational_number" title=3D"Irrational nu=
mber">irrational</a> mathematical constant <span class=3D"nowrap"><span cla=
ss=3D"texhtml"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E_(mathematical_con=
stant)" title=3D"E (mathematical constant)"><i>e</i></a> =E2=89=88 2.718281=
83 </span> ),</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml"> <i>b</i> =3D 2</span> (th=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_logarithm" title=3D"Binar=
y logarithm">binary logarithm</a>). In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
