<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Computations">Computations<=
/h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLogarithm&am=
p;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit section: Computations"><spa=
n>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></di=
v>
<p>The product and quotient of two positive numbers <span class=3D"texhtml =
mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">c</span> and <i><span class=3D"texhtml m=
var" style=3D"font-style:italic;">d</span></i> were routinely calculated as=
 the sum and difference of their logarithms. The product&nbsp;<span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>cd</i></span> or quotient&nbsp;<span class=3D"texhtml"><i>c=
</i>/<i>d</i></span> came from looking up the antilogarithm of the sum or d=
ifference, via the same table:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
