nnotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/711753605e98f4d42b75fe61254c3b8f311a5fd3" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:6.424ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle b^{=
x}=3Dy}"></span>. This function is called the base-<span class=3D"texhtml m=
var" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span> <i>logarithm function</i> or <i>=
logarithmic function</i> (or just <i>logarithm</i>).
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Characterization_by_the_pro=
duct_formula">Characterization by the product formula</h3><span class=3D"mw=
-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLogarithm&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;s=
ection=3D15" title=3D"Edit section: Characterization by the product formula=
"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></div>
<p>The function <span class=3D"texhtml">log<sub><i>b</i></sub>=E2=80=89<i>x=
</i></span> can also be essentially characterized by the product formula
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \log _{b}(xy)=3D\log _{b}x+\log _{b}y.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>log</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>b</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>log</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>b</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>log</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>b</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \log _{b}(xy)=
=3D\log _{b}x+\log _{b}y.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/4c1de92e0c333c4644f8866e417ea56e715324ec" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:25.868ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
log _{b}(xy)=3D\log _{b}x+\log _{b}y.}"></span>
</p><p>More precisely, the logarithm to any base <span class=3D"texhtml"><i=
>b</i> &gt; 1</span> is the only <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I=
ncreasing_function" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Increasing function">inc=
reasing function</a> <i>f</i> from the positive reals to the reals satisfyi=
ng <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>f</i>(<i>b</i>) =3D 1</span> and<sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-39" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log=
arithm#cite_note-39"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>36<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle f(xy)=3Df(x)+f(y).}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
