&amp;=3D\ln(t)+\ln(u).\end{aligned}}}"></span>
</p><p>The equality&nbsp;(1) splits the integral into two parts, while the =
equality&nbsp;(2) is a change of variable (<span class=3D"texhtml"><i>w</i>=
