qrt {2-{\sqrt {3}}}}}"></span> is not. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Almost_all" title=3D"Almost all">Almost all</a> real numbers are trans=
cendental. The logarithm is an example of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Transcendental_function" title=3D"Transcendental function">transc=
endental function</a>. The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gelfond=
%E2%80%93Schneider_theorem" title=3D"Gelfond=E2=80=93Schneider theorem">Gel=
fond=E2=80=93Schneider theorem</a> asserts that logarithms usually take tra=
nscendental, i.e. "difficult" values.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-47" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithm#cite_note-47"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>44<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Calculation">Calculation</h=
2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
