em;">=C3=97</span>10<sup>=E2=88=926</sup></span>. The quick convergence for=
 <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">z</span> close t=
o 1 can be taken advantage of in the following way: given a low-accuracy ap=
proximation <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>y</i> =E2=89=88 ln(<i>z</i>)</span> =
and putting
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
