<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Number_theory">Number theor=
y</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLogarithm&=
amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D34" title=3D"Edit section: Number theory"><=
span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span><=
/div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_logarithm" title=3D"Nat=
ural logarithm">Natural logarithms</a> are closely linked to <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime-counting_function" title=3D"Prime-counting=
 function">counting prime numbers</a> (2, 3, 5, 7, 11, ...), an important t=
opic in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory" title=3D"Nu=
mber theory">number theory</a>. For any <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Integer" title=3D"Integer">integer</a>&nbsp;<span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span>, the quantity of <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number" title=3D"Prime number">prime numbers=
</a> less than or equal to <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style=
:italic;">x</span> is denoted <span class=3D"texhtml"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime-counting_function" title=3D"Prime-counting functi=
on"><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=80</span>=
(<i>x</i>)</a></span>. The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_n=
umber_theorem" title=3D"Prime number theorem">prime number theorem</a> asse=
rts that <span class=3D"texhtml"><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font=
-style:italic;">=CF=80</span>(<i>x</i>)</span> is approximately given by
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle {\frac {x}{\ln(x)}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mi>x</mi>
            <mrow>
              <mi>ln</mi>
              <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {x}{\l=
n(x)}},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/3e7c35556de976b4896475a163d924bb9f3d83eb" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:6.561ex; height:5.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
frac {x}{\ln(x)}},}"></span>
</p><p>in the sense that the ratio of <span class=3D"texhtml"><span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=80</span>(<i>x</i>)</spa=
n> and that fraction approaches 1 when <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> tends to infinity.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-95" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithm#cite=
_note-95"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>90<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> As a consequence, the probability that a randomly cho=
sen number between 1 and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:i=
talic;">x</span> is prime is inversely <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Proportionality_(mathematics)" title=3D"Proportionality (mathematics)"=
>proportional</a> to the number of decimal digits of <span class=3D"texhtml=
 mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span>. A far better estimate of <spa=
n class=3D"texhtml"><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic=
;">=CF=80</span>(<i>x</i>)</span> is given by the <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Logarithmic_integral_function" title=3D"Logarithmic integra=
l function">offset logarithmic integral</a> function <span class=3D"texhtml=
">Li(<i>x</i>)</span>, defined by
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \mathrm {Li} (x)=3D\int _{2}^{x}{\frac {1}{\ln(t)}}\,dt=
.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">L</mi>
          <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">i</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msubsup>
          <mo>=E2=88=AB<!-- =E2=88=AB --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msubsup>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mi>ln</mi>
              <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>t</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mi>t</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathrm {Li} =
(x)=3D\int _{2}^{x}{\frac {1}{\ln(t)}}\,dt.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/da577950b8b4c4ef726a3065afcdafa378dbc3fb" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:20.875ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
mathrm {Li} (x)=3D\int _{2}^{x}{\frac {1}{\ln(t)}}\,dt.}"></span>
</p><p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riemann_hypothesis" tit=
le=3D"Riemann hypothesis">Riemann hypothesis</a>, one of the oldest open ma=
thematical <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjecture" title=3D"Co=
njecture">conjectures</a>, can be stated in terms of comparing <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=
=80</span>(<i>x</i>)</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml">Li(<i>x</i>)</span>=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-96" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Logarithm#cite_note-96"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>91<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Erd%C5%91s%E2%80%93Kac_theorem" title=3D"Erd=C5=91s=E2=80=
=93Kac theorem">Erd=C5=91s=E2=80=93Kac theorem</a> describing the number of=
 distinct <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_factor" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Prime factor">prime factors</a> also involves the <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_logarithm" title=3D"Natural lo=
garithm">natural logarithm</a>.
</p><p>The logarithm of <i>n</i> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/F=
actorial" title=3D"Factorial">factorial</a>, <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</=
i>! =3D 1 =C2=B7 2 =C2=B7 ... =C2=B7 <i>n</i></span>, is given by
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \ln(n!)=3D\ln(1)+\ln(2)+\cdots +\ln(n).}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>ln</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo>!</mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>ln</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>ln</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mo>=E2=8B=AF<!-- =E2=8B=AF --></mo>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>ln</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \ln(n!)=3D\ln=
(1)+\ln(2)+\cdots +\ln(n).}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/207af1498eca9a74c5e19ecab897d915d1052c95" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:35.746ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
ln(n!)=3D\ln(1)+\ln(2)+\cdots +\ln(n).}"></span>
</p><p>This can be used to obtain <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Stirling%27s_formula" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Stirling's formula">St=
irling's formula</a>, an approximation of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i>!=
</span> for large <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;"=
>n</span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-97" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithm#cite_note-97"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>92<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Generalizations">Generaliza=
