<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Complex_logarithm">Complex =
logarithm</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-=
bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLo=
garithm&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D36" title=3D"Edit section: Complex =
logarithm"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</s=
pan></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_logarithm" t=
itle=3D"Complex logarithm">Complex logarithm</a></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Complex_number_illustration_m=
ultiple_arguments.svg" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img alt=3D"An illustr=
ation of the polar form: a point is described by an arrow or equivalently b=
y its length and angle to the x-axis." src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/=
wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Complex_number_illustration_multiple_arguments=
.svg/250px-Complex_number_illustration_multiple_arguments.svg.png" decoding=
=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"266" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file=
-width=3D"204" data-file-height=3D"217"></a><figcaption>Polar form of <span=
 class=3D"texhtml"><i>z =3D x + iy</i></span>. Both <span class=3D"texhtml =
mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=86</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml=
 mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=86'</span> are arguments of <span c=
lass=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">z</span>.</figcaption></=
figure>
<p>All the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_number" title=
=3D"Complex number">complex numbers</a> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span> that solve the equation
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle e^{a}=3Dz}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>e</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>a</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>z</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle e^{a}=3Dz}</a=
nnotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/7dc3322ef38b06276c3bee59d656769b6edf531f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.338ex; width:6.372ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle e^=
{a}=3Dz}"></span>
</p><p>are called <i>complex logarithms</i> of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar"=
 style=3D"font-style:italic;">z</span>, when <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" s=
tyle=3D"font-style:italic;">z</span> is (considered as) a complex number. A=
 complex number is commonly represented as <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>z =3D=
 x + iy</i></span>, where <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:=
italic;">x</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ital=
ic;">y</span> are real numbers and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"fo=
nt-style:italic;">i</span> is an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I=
maginary_unit" title=3D"Imaginary unit">imaginary unit</a>, the square of w=
hich is =E2=88=921. Such a number can be visualized by a point in the <a hr=
