/span>
</p><p>It is related to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natura=
l_logarithm" title=3D"Natural logarithm">natural logarithm</a> by <span cla=
ss=3D"texhtml">Li<sub>1</sub>=E2=80=89(<i>z</i>) =3D =E2=88=92ln(1 =E2=88=
=92 <i>z</i>)</span>. Moreover, <span class=3D"texhtml">Li<sub><i>s</i></su=
b>=E2=80=89(1)</span> equals the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R=
iemann_zeta_function" title=3D"Riemann zeta function">Riemann zeta function=
</a> <span class=3D"texhtml">=CE=B6(<i>s</i>)</span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11=
3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithm#c=
ite_note-113"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>107<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
